    {
      "id": "73PmFf1SvCQa1RSCMot9m",
      "questionNumber": 5,
      "questionText": "The increasing order of reactivity of the following compounds towards reaction with alkyl halides directly is \n<img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/hp8LPFswHloTQ2jur/EdGyjr3WG0RQUimdvtm32MoU103JW/24m7gC4fejoKaFg8s8oHaY/image.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th January Morning Slot Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 217 English 1\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">(A)</h2>\n<img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/cgqcIAySpucFCDUyJ/P2VJdGJgSjynZe0XapICsnUUsI6YW/jUGGUVAfMtawkIZRNCwiSi/image.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th January Morning Slot Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 217 English 2\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">(B)</h2>\n<img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/ZTW1N1CNLcAG1bGp7/OZYvDyLC5c6xkm1TPsnkACUfSJJ1h/wrhFqR8lhLwqLNsxJZd7PO/image.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th January Morning Slot Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 217 English 3\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">(C)</h2>\n<img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/azOK8ctozFzI7StAi/zwbKilYwleJvHQP9L7CMvbT38rBVu/3ZrfwHBcroT8raYLZTFrDZ/image.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th January Morning Slot Chemistry - Compounds Containing Nitrogen Question 217 English 4\">\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center\">(D)</h2>\n",
      "options": [
        "A &lt; B &lt; C &lt; D",
        "B &lt; A &lt; C &lt; D",
        "B &lt; A &lt; D &lt; C",
        "A &lt; C &lt; D &lt; B"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "aromatic-amines",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Lone pair over nitrogen will act as the reacting centre and more free nitrogen atom will be more reactive towards alkyl halide.\n<br><br>For compound (A), lone pair of N atom is in resonance with $$\\pi $$ bond of C = O. So lone pair of N atom gets delocalised.\n<br><br>For compound (B), lone pair of N atom is in resonance with $$\\pi $$ bond of  two C = O. So here lone pair of N atom gets more delocalised than compound (A). So reactivity towards alkyl halide is very less for this compound.\n<br><br>For compound (C), lone pair of N atom is in resonance with $$\\pi $$ bond of  benzene ring and $$\\pi $$ bond of C $$ \\equiv $$ N. So delocalisation of lone pair of N atom is relatively high.\n<br><br>For compound (D), lone pair of N atom is in resonance with $$\\pi $$ bond of  benzene ring only. So delocalisation of lone pair of N atom is relatively low.\n<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ Reactivity order is B &lt; A &lt; C &lt; D.",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
